<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-10-31T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-10-31T15:00:00-05:00" n="195" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d195">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">851.4061 Motion Pictures/230:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Straus</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-31T15:00:00-05:00">October 31, 1935—3
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>441. Your 929, October 30, noon. I wish to convey to you and your
                                staff my hearty congratulations for the manner in which the motion
                                picture question has been handled.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>